Create React app in the frontend folder: npx create-react-app frontend
Run React dev server: npm start
Add a Bootswatch file (bootstrap.min.css) in the src folder.
Install React-Bootstrap: npm i react-bootstrap

Add font awesome CDN link in the index.html.

Install React Router: npm i react-router-dom react-router-bootstrap

In the root folder: npm init
Install Express in the root folder: npm i express
Run backend: node backend/server

Install axios: npm i axios

Add a proxy in the frontend package.json.

Install nodemon and concurrently: npm i -D nodemon concurrently
Install dotenv: npm i dotenv

Create a file named ".env" in the root folder.

Create a cluster on mongodb.com.

Install mongoose: npm i mongoose

Redux Thunk: With a plain basic Redux store, you can only do simple synchronous updates by dispatching an action.
Middleware extends the store's abilities, and lets you write async logic that interacts with the store.